React Query â€”> alias TanStack Query
- A React library which handles fetching more efficiently
- Handles caching and cache invalidation behind the scenes automatically. 
- Handles refetching via â€œreFetchOnWindowFocus: trueâ€
- useInfiniteQuery() â€”>  for infinite scrolling data. 
- Optimistic Updates 
Other Info â€”> 
Global State â€”> to avoid prop drilling to multiple levels, we can make a global state using Context API or Redux. 
Key Prop â€”> every item in the list should have a unique identifier named key. So that React knows exactly which element is to be updated, removed or whatever. 
Event Handling â€”> directly reference the function inline inside the curly braces with camelCase event name. Like onClick={handleClick}, onSubmit{handleSubmit}, onChange{handleChange} etc. 
Conditional rendering â€”> using Tertary operator, && or || 
Curly Braces â€”> We can add dynamic JS variables, functions etc in JSX but only inside curly braces. So, everything dynamic Js would go under curly braces. Like {variable}, {function}. 
